04:29.436 --> 04:30.636
All right?
- No problem.

04:30.738 --> 04:31.803
Thanks, Joe!

04:31.905 --> 04:33.772
<i> - Here's what I know.</i>

04:33.841 --> 04:36.475
<i> There can be no dead Benji</i>
<i> for you to mourn.</i>

04:36.543 --> 04:38.243
<i> He needs to disappear.</i>

04:38.345 --> 04:41.346
<i> Already handled the optics</i>
<i> on social media--</i>

04:41.415 --> 04:44.850
<i> portrait of a dude hard</i>
<i> partying his way off the grid.</i>

04:44.952 --> 04:47.152
<i> As for the body--</i>

04:47.254 --> 04:49.554
<i> cremation seems expedient.</i>

04:49.657 --> 04:51.556
<i> This will require chemicals,</i>

04:51.625 --> 04:55.994
<i> a steady blaze, and absolutely</i>
<i> no dental records.</i>

04:56.096 --> 04:58.964
<i> [tense music]</i>

04:59.033 --> 05:02.834
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:02.936 --> 05:04.336
[mallet thuds on floor]

05:04.405 --> 05:06.371
Bluuh...
[liquid splashes]

05:06.473 --> 05:08.340
[coughs]
<i> It looks like</i>

05:08.442 --> 05:12.044
<i> I'm gonna need to slow</i>
<i> the biological roll on Benji.</i>

05:12.112 --> 05:14.012
<i> It's about temperature,</i>
<i> and it's about humidity.</i>

05:14.114 --> 05:17.582
<i> And dropping the temp this low</i>
<i> puts the books at risk--</i>

05:17.685 --> 05:20.719
<i> dry, brittle, lost forever.</i>

05:20.821 --> 05:23.088
<i> My humidifiers</i>
<i> won't let that happen.</i>

05:23.190 --> 05:25.157
<i> Gertrude Stein is dead.</i>

05:25.259 --> 05:28.293
<i> She's not coming back</i>
<i> to sign books.</i>

05:28.395 --> 05:30.996
<i> Hopefully, this holds him</i>
<i> until I can man up</i>

05:31.098 --> 05:32.698
<i> and do the deed.</i>

