money for books.

10:07.841 --> 10:09.374
Just between us.

10:09.476 --> 10:11.042
- Yeah. No problem.

10:11.111 --> 10:13.245
Between us.
What do you need?

10:13.313 --> 10:15.847
- Well, you might have to
run to a few different places.

10:20.754 --> 10:23.021
- You can count on me, Joe.

10:23.123 --> 10:26.358
<i> [dark music]</i>

10:26.460 --> 10:27.926
- Thanks, Pac.

10:30.364 --> 10:33.698
- The swine and I.

10:33.801 --> 10:36.401
Eye to eye.

10:37.838 --> 10:40.672
My heart is his.

10:40.774 --> 10:42.774
And that...

10:42.876 --> 10:44.276
was sunset.

10:50.617 --> 10:52.284
- I'm not sure it had
the vigilance or depth

10:52.386 --> 10:55.420
that you're capable of.
I just wasn't fully invested.

10:55.522 --> 10:57.923
- Interesting, Blythe.

10:58.025 --> 11:00.525
How do we maintain
the reader's attention?

11:00.627 --> 11:03.094
We infuse the universal

11:03.197 --> 11:05.130
with painful specificity,

11:05.232 --> 11:06.598
or they simply turn the page.

11:06.700 --> 11:08.333
- Exactly.

11:08.435 --> 11:11.670
My worst fear--and I'm not
commenting on Yuri's poem,

11:11.738 --> 11:15.440
per se, is not to be bad
but unremarkable.

11:15.542 --> 11:18.510
- Unremarkable.
That is the fear.

11:18.612 --> 11:21.112
I hope this was helpful,
Yuri.

11:21.215 --> 11:22.981
I think that does it
for today.

11:23.083 --> 11:24.816
Next up is...Blythe.

11:24.918 --> 11:26.284
And Beck.

11:26.386 --> 11:28.553
Send a piece of your choosing
to myself

11:28.655 --> 11:30.889
and your fellow classmates,
and we'll review on Thursday.

11:30.991 --> 11:33.792
<i> [lightly edgy music]</i>

11:33.894 --> 11:40.799
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:55.682 --> 11:57.415
[bed creaking]

11:57.484 --> 11:59.150
<i> - Here's what I've gleaned</i>

11:59.253 --> 12:01.887
<i> from this little exercise</i>
<i> in futility, Beck.</i>

12:01.955 --> 12:03.855
<i> You're in no mood to write.</i>

12:03.957 --> 12:05.824
[creak, snap, thud]

12:05.926 --> 12:08.026
<i> - And you need a new bed.</i>

12:08.128 --> 12:10.428
<i> So, hey,</i>
<i> maybe your enthusiastic</i>

12:10.530 --> 12:12.097
<i> but ultimately empty encounter</i>

12:12.165 --> 12:13.398
<i> with that Warby Parker-wearing</i>
<i> mixologist</i>

12:13.500 --> 12:15.066
<i> could work to our advantage.</i>

12:15.135 --> 12:16.167
<i> Any chance you're down</i>
<i> for shopping trip?</i>

12:16.270 --> 12:17.335
<i> I've got time to kill</i>

12:17.404 --> 12:19.704
<i> while Paco's out shopping.</i>

12:22.643 --> 12:24.876
<i> - You read my mind.</i>

12:24.945 --> 12:26.678
<i> - Pick you up in an hour.</i>

12:26.780 --> 12:28.947
<i> But I have to play this</i>
<i> perfectly,</i>

12:29.049 --> 12:31.149
<i> and in order to do that,</i>

12:31.251 --> 12:32.751
<i> I gotta break out</i>
<i> the big gun.</i>

12:32.853 --> 12:35.053
[engine revs]

12:35.122 --> 12:37.555
<i> Mr. Mooney's Buick Skylark.</i>

12:37.624 --> 12:39.658
<i> - ♪ Girl, you think</i>
<i> you got it bad... ♪</i>

12:39.760 --> 12:41.192
<i> - You bound down the stairs</i>
<i> in those tight,</i>

12:41.295 --> 12:42.627
<i> not-too-tight jeans.</i>

12:42.696 --> 12:43.962
<i> You're in flip-flops</i>

12:44.064 --> 12:45.330
<i> and your toenails sparkle</i>

12:45.399 --> 12:46.998
<i> and your hair's in a bun,</i>

12:47.100 --> 12:48.433
<i> and, hey, at least you</i>
<i> don't have any hickeys.</i>

12:48.535 --> 12:50.535
<i> So there's that.</i>

12:50.637 --> 12:54.906
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:55.008 --> 12:58.276
- Oh, my God, I can't
believe this is your car.

12:58.378 --> 13:00.312
You're a lifesaver.

13:00.380 --> 13:01.913
[kiss]
No idea how much

13:02.015 --> 13:03.915
I needed a new bed.

13:07.020 --> 13:10.355
<i> - ♪ Girl, you think</i>
<i> you got it bad... ♪</i>

13:10.424 --> 13:12.223
<i> ♪ Do do do do do do do ♪</i>

13:12.326 --> 13:15.794
[engine humming]

13:17.230 --> 13:20.098
<i> [Muzak plays in background]</i>

13:20.200 --> 13:21.866
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:21.969 --> 13:23.969
<i> - New Challenge.</i>

13:24.071 --> 13:26.905
<i> How do I segue this from</i>

13:27.007 --> 13:28.840
<i> browsing glassware to...</i>

13:28.942 --> 13:31.309
<i> "Holy shit! Joe's the one"?</i>

13:33.413 --> 13:35.480
- Weird.
[small laugh]

13:35.582 --> 13:38.149
I have one just like this.

13:38.218 --> 13:40.251
<i> - Yeah, I-I know</i>
<i> all about it.</i>

13:40.354 --> 13:43.254
<i> Benji told me.</i>
- It was my dad's.

13:43.323 --> 13:45.023
<i> - The infamous red ladle.</i>

13:45.125 --> 13:46.992
<i> How you like to be spanked</i>
<i> with it.</i>

13:47.094 --> 13:49.794
<i> Is that what</i>
<i> you really want, Beck?</i>

13:49.896 --> 13:52.931
<i> Is that the guy</i>
<i> you're looking for?</i>

13:53.033 --> 13:55.066
<i> [edgy music]</i>

13:55.168 --> 13:57.569
<i> Just pick one.</i>

13:57.671 --> 13:59.838
<i> It's all cut from the same</i>
<i> hunk of overpriced wood.</i>

13:59.940 --> 14:01.873
- I can't decide.

14:01.942 --> 14:03.842
<i> - People trying to buy some</i>
<i> sort of meaning in their lives</i>

14:03.910 --> 14:06.911
<i> with $60 candles</i>
<i> and sustainable lamps.</i>

14:07.014 --> 14:08.346
They all look
pretty good to me.

14:08.448 --> 14:10.648
- No, I just mean
should I get the queen

14:10.751 --> 14:12.450
or the king-size bed?

14:12.552 --> 14:14.652
- Your bedroom isn't big
enough to fit a king.

14:14.755 --> 14:18.289
- You're right, it's too...

14:18.392 --> 14:21.793
How do you know that?

14:21.895 --> 14:23.561
- It's New York.

14:23.663 --> 14:26.064
No one's bedroom is
big enough to fit a king.

14:26.166 --> 14:27.832
[phone chimes]

14:27.934 --> 14:30.068
- Ugh...

14:30.170 --> 14:31.302
[sighs]

14:31.371 --> 14:32.637
- What's wrong?

14:32.739 --> 14:34.472
- This girl, Blythe,
in workshop,

14:34.541 --> 14:36.241
she just submitted
her short story.

14:38.712 --> 14:39.911
- And?
- And I haven't even

14:40.013 --> 14:41.946
started mine yet,
and it's due tomorrow.

14:43.950 --> 14:46.684
[murmurs]

14:46.787 --> 14:48.486
Hers...

14:48.588 --> 14:50.221
it's brilliant.

14:50.323 --> 14:54.125
It's about a crow that flies
into a woman's house,

14:54.194 --> 14:56.428
runs into the walls,
and leaves blood everywhere.

14:56.530 --> 14:58.696
- That sounds terrible.

14:58.799 --> 15:00.398
- Read it.

15:10.510 --> 15:12.377
Well?

15:15.015 --> 15:16.614
- You might be right.
- Ugh!

15:16.716 --> 15:18.883
I know.

15:22.923 --> 15:24.656
Can I ask you something?

15:24.724 --> 15:26.157
- Anything.

15:26.259 --> 15:28.793
- Promise to tell the truth?

15:28.895 --> 15:30.261
- Scout's honor.

15:30.363 --> 15:33.298
<i> [soft music]</i>

15:33.400 --> 15:35.066
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:35.135 --> 15:38.169
- Do you think...
I'm unremarkable?

15:38.271 --> 15:45.310
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:47.013 --> 15:48.813
- Unremarkable people
don't worry

15:48.915 --> 15:50.982
about being unremarkable.

15:53.653 --> 15:56.187
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:56.289 --> 15:59.824
<i> - ♪ Only for you</i>
<i> we should call it ♪</i>

15:59.893 --> 16:01.726
<i> ♪ A straight love affair ♪</i>

16:01.828 --> 16:03.228
<i> ♪ I suppose... ♪</i>

16:03.330 --> 16:04.829
<i> - This is it, Beck.</i>

16:04.898 --> 16:06.197
<i> This is the moment</i>
<i> I'm gonna show you</i>

16:06.299 --> 16:08.066
<i> just how remarkable you are.</i>

16:08.135 --> 16:09.801
<i> You want down and dirty,</i>
<i> you got it.</i>

16:09.903 --> 16:12.170
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:12.272 --> 16:14.939
<i> - ♪ Palms that may</i>
<i> hold you... ♪</i>

16:15.008 --> 16:16.908
- [gasps]
[whispers] Stop, Joe, stop!

16:17.010 --> 16:18.176
- What? I--What?
I thought that you--

16:18.278 --> 16:19.711
- That I wanted to get
arrested

16:19.813 --> 16:22.080
while you're going
all bush diver on me in public?

16:22.182 --> 16:24.916
That's not exactly
on my to-do list today.

16:27.687 --> 16:30.188
<i> - I guess I read that wrong.</i>

16:33.260 --> 16:35.960
<i> You haven't made eye contact</i>
<i> for the past ten minutes.</i>

16:36.029 --> 16:37.962
<i> Things couldn't get</i>
<i> any worse right now.</i>

16:38.031 --> 16:41.199
[phone buzzing]

16:41.301 --> 16:43.401
Hello?
<i> - Hey, Joe, it's Ethan.</i>

16:43.470 --> 16:45.069
<i> Ethan from the bookstore.</i>
- Yeah, yeah, I know

16:45.172 --> 16:46.538
who you are, Ethan.

16:46.640 --> 16:50.675
- Right. Thing is,
the power's out. Um...

16:50.744 --> 16:53.244
the electrician says he thinks
the system is overloaded,

16:53.313 --> 16:54.879
but he can't get
to the fuse box because...

16:54.981 --> 16:56.614
<i> - It's in the basement</i>
<i> with a dead body.</i>

16:56.716 --> 16:58.883
- Which is locked.
He thinks he can pop the lock,

16:58.985 --> 17:00.485
but I just wanted to--

17:00.587 --> 17:02.720
- No! No, no, no, no, no!
Just--Just--

17:02.822 --> 17:04.189
just tell the electrician
to go home.

17:04.291 --> 17:05.990
I'll call him later.
You lock up and go home.

17:06.059 --> 17:07.592
I'll deal with it
when I get back.

17:07.694 --> 17:09.427
All right?

17:09.529 --> 17:10.962
Okay.

17:13.166 --> 17:15.033
- Everything okay?
- Yeah, it's fine.

17:15.135 --> 17:17.135
It's fine. It's just
a little problem at the shop.

17:17.237 --> 17:19.070
I should get you...home.

17:19.172 --> 17:21.472
<i> [edgy music]</i>

17:21.541 --> 17:23.274
<i> I was afraid</i>
<i> this might happen.</i>

17:23.343 --> 17:25.743
<i> Six humidifiers and an AC unit</i>
<i> from the late '70s</i>

17:25.845 --> 17:27.478
<i> cranked to its lowest</i>
<i> setting...</i>

17:27.581 --> 17:31.182
<i> even in death, Benji is</i>
<i> a colossal pain in my ass.</i>

17:34.069 --> 17:36.102
<i> [dark music]</i>

17:36.171 --> 17:38.705
<i> - Okay. With the AC out,</i>

17:38.774 --> 17:43.043
<i> seems deterioration speeds</i>
<i> really picked up.</i>

17:43.145 --> 17:46.613
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:46.715 --> 17:49.449
[heavy exhale]

17:55.223 --> 17:58.458
<i> Oh! Is that...ooze?</i>

17:58.527 --> 17:59.993
[groaning]

18:00.095 --> 18:01.628
[coughing]
<i> Things have grown</i>

18:01.697 --> 18:04.097
<i> biologically dire</i>
<i> in the Benji department.</i>

18:04.166 --> 18:05.966
<i> Also the rare book department.</i>

18:06.068 --> 18:10.437
<i> But...I can't protect them</i>
<i> until I get rid of him.</i>

18:10.539 --> 18:13.473
<i> Benji has to go.</i>

18:13.575 --> 18:16.776
<i> [dark music]</i>

18:16.878 --> 18:18.478
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:18.580 --> 18:20.480
[groaning]

18:28.890 --> 18:29.956
[snap]
Ugh!

18:30.058 --> 18:31.024
[phone chimes]

18:33.996 --> 18:35.862
<i> - Hey, what are you up to?</i>

18:35.964 --> 18:38.365
<i> Do you happen to read Chinese?</i>

18:38.467 --> 18:40.967
<i> Or own a mallet?</i>

18:41.069 --> 18:44.604
<i> [unsettling music]</i>

18:44.673 --> 18:46.506
<i> - The books were safe.</i>

18:46.608 --> 18:48.141
<i> Basement</i>
<i> is 100% corpse-free.</i>

18:48.243 --> 18:49.576
<i> Can't burn the body</i>
<i> in daylight anyway,</i>

18:49.644 --> 18:51.177
<i> so the least Benji can do</i>

18:51.279 --> 18:53.046
<i> is wait in the car</i>
<i> for a little while.</i>

18:53.148 --> 18:57.784
<i> [light guitar strumming]</i>

18:57.886 --> 18:59.185
Ready for that.
- Okay.

18:59.287 --> 19:01.221
- Let go for a second.

19:01.323 --> 19:03.390
- Okay.
- Yeah.

19:03.492 --> 19:05.025
- It's in the peg!
- Okay.

19:05.127 --> 19:06.593
[both laugh]

19:06.695 --> 19:09.095
Hand me the mallet.
- Yeah. Ah!

19:13.201 --> 19:14.734
- Should be good.

19:14.836 --> 19:17.637
<i> [light music continues]</i>

19:17.739 --> 19:24.844
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:28.150 --> 19:30.150
- [laughing]
- There it is.

19:30.218 --> 19:31.651
Go!

19:31.753 --> 19:32.819
- [laughing]

19:32.888 --> 19:34.421
Say when.

19:36.691 --> 19:38.491
- When. I think--when.
When, when, when.

19:38.593 --> 19:39.859
- [giggling]

19:44.466 --> 19:46.866
Cheers to us.
[glasses clink]

19:46.968 --> 19:48.935
- You make a good
apprentice.

19:49.037 --> 19:53.006
- I was gonna say
the same thing about you.

19:57.112 --> 20:01.281
I'm sorry about earlier.
I didn't mean to get so upset.

20:01.383 --> 20:02.782
- [murmurs]

20:02.884 --> 20:04.717
It's okay.

20:04.820 --> 20:07.454
- No, it's not, it's just...

20:07.556 --> 20:11.491
I don't want you
to think of me

20:11.593 --> 20:14.427
like that.

20:20.068 --> 20:24.237
- I...like you, Joe.

20:24.339 --> 20:27.807
Like actually...like.

20:27.909 --> 20:32.245
<i> [soft music]</i>

20:32.347 --> 20:34.914
And I was a little
in my head, to be honest.

20:35.016 --> 20:38.485
Blythe's short story kinda
threw me for a loop.

20:38.587 --> 20:40.053
- It's not a competition.

20:40.155 --> 20:41.855
- I know, but...

20:41.957 --> 20:44.491
I wonder...

20:44.559 --> 20:48.061
am I ever gonna write
anything that amazing?

20:48.163 --> 20:50.063
- You're talented.

20:50.165 --> 20:51.831
- You don't know that.
- I--I know--

20:51.900 --> 20:55.268
I know you need to
get out of your head and...

20:55.370 --> 20:58.972
forget Blythe,
this Blythe person.

20:59.074 --> 21:01.207
Forget everybody.
Just write what you want.

21:01.309 --> 21:04.611
- God! Everyone says that
like it's so easy.

21:04.679 --> 21:06.312
- [laughs] I know, I know.

21:06.414 --> 21:08.948
Okay, so, um...

21:09.050 --> 21:10.783
pop quiz.

21:10.886 --> 21:11.851
Don't think.

21:12.888 --> 21:14.087
Just answer.

21:14.189 --> 21:16.022
- Okay.

21:16.124 --> 21:18.091
- What hits you
like a gut punch when you--

21:18.193 --> 21:19.692
the first thought?
[ice cubes clatter]

21:19.761 --> 21:21.661
- My dad.

21:21.763 --> 21:24.030
Before he...

21:24.132 --> 21:26.866
- Yeah. Right.

21:26.968 --> 21:28.468
Of course.

21:32.274 --> 21:34.307
- He was an addict.

21:34.409 --> 21:37.343
It was hard...

21:37.412 --> 21:39.345
and scary.

21:41.483 --> 21:44.350
I mean, there were
good days too.

21:44.452 --> 21:48.121
Like I always knew
it was gonna be one of those

21:48.190 --> 21:53.426
when I woke up to the smell
of pancakes cooking.

21:53.495 --> 21:57.864
He used this red ladle
to scoop up the batter.

21:57.933 --> 22:01.000
<i> - This is the red ladle</i>
<i> story?</i>

22:01.102 --> 22:03.236
<i> [soft music]</i>

22:03.305 --> 22:06.105
- And I would be...
laughing,

22:06.208 --> 22:08.441
singing along to some

22:08.543 --> 22:11.678
bad Top 40 song.

22:11.780 --> 22:14.480
And everything
would be...right.

22:14.583 --> 22:19.085
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:19.187 --> 22:22.922
But then he'd...
he'd go out and...

22:23.024 --> 22:26.492
the ladle would go back
in the drawer.

22:26.595 --> 22:30.263
And I'd wait
for the next good day.

22:33.001 --> 22:37.537
Until there weren't
any more.

22:37.639 --> 22:38.771
[small laugh]

22:38.873 --> 22:40.840
Wow!

22:40.909 --> 22:44.310
I did<i> not</i> expect
to say all that.

22:44.379 --> 22:46.112
- I think you're right.
You definitely don't have

22:46.181 --> 22:48.648
anything meaningful
to write about.

22:48.717 --> 22:52.218
<i> Ohh. Benji was wrong</i>
<i> about all of it.</i>

22:52.287 --> 22:55.388
<i> His whole red ladle story.</i>
<i> You don't wanna be spanked.</i>

22:55.490 --> 22:57.523
<i> You wanna feel safe,</i>

22:57.626 --> 22:59.292
<i> loved.</i>

22:59.361 --> 23:02.395
<i> You want someone to make</i>
<i> pancakes for you.</i>

23:02.497 --> 23:05.265
<i> [quiet music]</i>

23:05.367 --> 23:12.171
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:20.548 --> 23:24.384
<i> [lighthearted music]</i>

23:24.452 --> 23:26.919
[knocking on door]

23:27.022 --> 23:28.521
- Um...

23:28.623 --> 23:30.523
hold that thought.
I'll be right back.

23:30.625 --> 23:33.293
[knocking continues]
Coming!

23:35.830 --> 23:38.398
Is everything okay?
- No!

23:38.500 --> 23:41.167
<i> - Peach. I should have known.</i>
- Thank God you're here.

23:41.269 --> 23:43.169
I'm having a really
bad flare-up.

23:43.271 --> 23:45.705
I think I need you to take me
to the emergency room.

23:47.375 --> 23:49.075
Oh...Joseph.

23:49.177 --> 23:50.810
I didn't realize you were here.

23:50.912 --> 23:53.146
- I told you he was coming.

23:53.248 --> 23:55.381
Uh, Peach
is really sick.

23:55.450 --> 23:58.151
- This is probably more
than you need to know,

23:58.253 --> 24:00.386
but...I have a rare
chronic bladder disease

24:00.455 --> 24:01.788
called interstitial
cystitis--

24:01.890 --> 24:04.157
[groans]
Oh...gosh!

24:04.259 --> 24:07.160
I mean, you know, some
people think I'm being uppity,

24:07.262 --> 24:10.163
but...I can't have
any fast food.

24:10.231 --> 24:13.032
And if I drink, it has to
be a high PH, you know,

24:13.134 --> 24:15.034
like Ketel One or Goose

24:15.103 --> 24:16.836
and pear juice.

24:16.938 --> 24:19.238
- Weren't you doing Jager
shots at your party?

24:19.341 --> 24:20.773
- Oh--oh!

24:20.875 --> 24:22.608
- Let's get you
to the hospital.

24:22.677 --> 24:24.677
- Yeah.
- And Joe has a car.

24:24.779 --> 24:26.379
He can take us.
Right, Joe?

24:26.481 --> 24:28.047
[softly]
You can take us?

24:28.149 --> 24:29.515
- Of course.

24:30.752 --> 24:33.019
<i> I mean, I've got a dead body</i>
<i> in the trunk,</i>

24:33.088 --> 24:34.153
<i> but, hey, no biggie, right?</i>

24:34.255 --> 24:35.722
- Oh, this is taking forever!

24:35.790 --> 24:38.291
I mean, he took the worst
street to get across town.

24:38.393 --> 24:39.726
- Be nice.

24:39.828 --> 24:41.694
- I'm in real pain!

24:41.796 --> 24:43.563
- [mouthing]
I'm sorry.

24:45.367 --> 24:47.500
- Ohh...Joseph...

24:47.602 --> 24:49.335
- Yep.
- I'm feeling nauseated.

24:49.437 --> 24:51.604
Can you crack a window?
There's like a...

24:51.673 --> 24:54.540
sort of putrid aroma that keeps
wafting in the backseat.

24:54.642 --> 24:57.210
- What can I say?
The smells of the city.

24:57.312 --> 25:00.179
<i> [edgy music]</i>

25:00.281 --> 25:02.181
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:02.283 --> 25:03.282
- Oh...God.

25:03.351 --> 25:04.784
I can't deal.
I can't deal.

25:04.886 --> 25:06.853
We'll walk!

25:09.657 --> 25:11.090
- I'm so sorry.

25:15.797 --> 25:17.497
<i> - It's almost</i>
<i> the witching hour.</i>

25:17.599 --> 25:19.999
<i> Grab the supplies.</i>
<i> Drive the narcissistic cadaver</i>

25:20.101 --> 25:21.801
<i> formerly known as Benji</i>
<i> to his final destination,</i>

25:21.870 --> 25:25.471
<i> light a match,</i>
<i> and I'm yours forever, Beck.</i>

25:27.809 --> 25:30.343
<i> Well, this is a development.</i>

25:30.445 --> 25:31.811
- That's him.

25:31.913 --> 25:34.747
<i> [intense music]</i>

25:34.849 --> 25:36.849
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:39.284 --> 25:40.216
- Potassium nitrate.

25:40.318 --> 25:41.751
Six rolls of duct tape.

25:41.853 --> 25:44.620
Fire starter, twine,
burlap, wood stakes.

25:44.722 --> 25:46.689
You wanna explain
what all this is for?

25:46.791 --> 25:48.424
<i> - Explain the shopping list</i>

25:48.493 --> 25:51.527
<i> straight out of</i>
<i> "Body Disposal for Dummies"?</i>

25:51.629 --> 25:53.663
I know.

25:53.731 --> 25:55.298
I know how this all must look.

25:55.400 --> 25:57.733
I know involving Paco
was the wrong thing to do.

25:57.835 --> 26:00.903
But th-things have been
a little crazy for me lately.

26:01.005 --> 26:03.539
I guess I was hoping I could
make the world a better place.

26:03.608 --> 26:07.944
<i> [tense music]</i>

26:08.046 --> 26:09.946
You know--It...

26:10.048 --> 26:13.783
it would--it would just
be easier if I show you.

26:15.753 --> 26:17.887
Yeah, I'll show you.
Come on.

26:21.059 --> 26:23.259
Technically, we're not allowed
to plant anything in here.

26:23.361 --> 26:26.162
I was just trying to keep it
a bit under wraps.

26:26.264 --> 26:27.563
- And the chemicals?

26:27.665 --> 26:29.031
- They dissolve roots.

26:29.100 --> 26:31.534
-Fire starters?

26:31.603 --> 26:33.703
- I like to grill.

26:36.074 --> 26:37.473
Here.

26:44.582 --> 26:45.848
- It's good.

26:45.950 --> 26:47.083
- Thank you.

26:47.151 --> 26:49.051
- So he built a garden.
So what?

26:49.153 --> 26:52.088
I told this guy--stay away
from my girlfriend's kid.

26:52.156 --> 26:55.458
And what does he do? He gives
him money for errands?

26:57.295 --> 26:59.195
- Hey, I told you,
I'm a parole officer, okay?

26:59.297 --> 27:00.830
We see guys like this
all the time.

27:00.932 --> 27:04.133
He's a sicko.
I feel it in my gut.

27:04.235 --> 27:06.802
Hey, will you get back
inside, Paco?

27:06.904 --> 27:09.405
Just tell your mom I'm gonna
be right there, okay, buddy?

27:09.507 --> 27:12.408
All right, all right,
all right.

27:12.477 --> 27:15.411
Kid's got ADHD.
Tough to manage at times.

27:15.480 --> 27:17.380
But that's what makes him
vulnerable to freaks like this.

27:17.448 --> 27:20.082
- Look, I apologize
if I crossed the line.

27:20.151 --> 27:22.752
I just noticed how hungry
Paco is all the time, you know?

27:22.820 --> 27:25.187
I gave him a few dollars
to go to the store, honestly,

27:25.256 --> 27:26.822
so he could buy himself
a sandwich.

27:26.924 --> 27:29.825
I lend him books from time
to time, too--that's all.

27:29.894 --> 27:32.161
Just seems a little neglected.

27:32.263 --> 27:34.830
- You kidding me right now?
- I'm not saying they're unfit.

27:34.899 --> 27:36.599
A lot of people drink--
- All right, that's it--

27:36.701 --> 27:38.401
- All right, all right,
all right.

27:38.503 --> 27:40.536
Sorry to have
taken up your time.

27:40.605 --> 27:42.338
Good luck with
the garden.

27:42.440 --> 27:45.374
- Thank you, Officer.
<i> People. They're easy to fool.</i>

27:45.443 --> 27:47.843
<i> Like these cops. I'm the nice,</i>
<i> straight-edge guy.</i>

27:47.912 --> 27:49.645
<i> So there's nothing</i>
<i> to worry about.</i>

27:49.747 --> 27:52.114
<i> People believe whatever</i>
<i> supports their world-view.</i>

27:52.216 --> 27:54.850
<i> Unfortunately, that seems</i>
<i> to include you, Beck.</i>

27:54.952 --> 27:58.154
<i> You believed you deserved</i>
<i> Benji and his neglect,</i>

27:58.222 --> 28:00.122
<i> and you believe you deserve</i>
<i> Peach and her drama</i>

28:00.191 --> 28:01.824
<i> and on and on.</i>

28:01.926 --> 28:04.293
<i> I want to call and tell you,</i>
<i> but I can't,</i>

28:04.395 --> 28:06.662
<i> because there's a traditional</i>
<i> waiting period</i>

28:06.764 --> 28:08.030
<i> between every goddamn</i>
<i> communication</i>

28:08.099 --> 28:10.032
<i> when trying to date someone.</i>

28:10.134 --> 28:12.635
<i> I hate this generation.</i>

28:12.737 --> 28:16.539
<i> [unsettling music]</i>

28:16.641 --> 28:23.446
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:44.068 --> 28:45.267
- Thank you.

28:46.771 --> 28:48.204
[sighs]

28:48.306 --> 28:49.739
Thanks for
staying with me.

28:49.841 --> 28:51.841
Honestly, I...
I don't know

28:51.943 --> 28:53.676
what I would have done
without you.

28:53.745 --> 28:56.779
- You can always
count on me.

28:56.881 --> 28:58.180
- Thanks.

29:00.618 --> 29:03.085
- So what do you think
about Joe?

29:05.390 --> 29:07.623
- Uh...yeah, you know,
I like him.

29:07.725 --> 29:09.892
- I think I might
really like him.

29:09.994 --> 29:12.762
I mean, I wasn't sure
if I was ready to get involved,

29:12.864 --> 29:15.264
but...maybe?
- Okay, you can't be serious.

29:15.366 --> 29:19.235
I mean, the guy
works at a bookstore.

29:19.303 --> 29:23.272
[laughs]
Beck, look, I know you.

29:23.374 --> 29:25.608
You don't wanna spend
your fifth anniversary

29:25.710 --> 29:29.078
going Dutch
at Katz's Deli.

29:29.147 --> 29:32.348
You need someone
to take care of you.

29:32.450 --> 29:36.285
so you can write,
be free,

29:36.387 --> 29:38.287
happy.

29:38.389 --> 29:42.158
Not someone like Joe
and his financial limitations.

29:42.260 --> 29:44.260
- That is not fair.

29:44.328 --> 29:46.395
- Nobody pays me
to be fair.

29:47.298 --> 29:49.165
What do you say we get
a bite to eat?

29:49.233 --> 29:53.102
'Cause I'm starving.
- I think I better skip it.

29:53.204 --> 29:55.371
I should really
get home.

29:55.473 --> 29:57.640
Glad you're feeling
better.

30:08.820 --> 30:13.823
[phone buzzing]

30:13.925 --> 30:16.759
- Oh, no.
No, not--not now.

30:16.861 --> 30:18.427
Okay, Beck.
All right.

30:18.529 --> 30:20.763
Hey.
How's the patient?

30:20.865 --> 30:23.232
- Better.
Thanks for the ride.

30:23.334 --> 30:25.501
The doctor said it was good
that we came when we did.

30:25.603 --> 30:27.536
- Oh, yeah?

30:27.605 --> 30:30.906
- Why don't you meet me
back at my place?

30:31.008 --> 30:32.942
Maybe we can pick up
where we left off?

30:33.044 --> 30:34.310
- What about Peach?

30:34.412 --> 30:36.679
- What about her?
- Where is she now?

30:36.781 --> 30:37.880
- Indochine.

30:37.982 --> 30:39.715
<i> It's her comfort food.</i>

30:39.817 --> 30:41.617
<i> [dramatic musical sting]</i>
<i> Joe: Perfect.</i>

30:41.719 --> 30:43.953
<i> Peach is gulping steamed</i>
<i> Chilean Sea Bass</i>

30:44.055 --> 30:46.322
<i> down her scrawny gullet,</i>
<i> and I'm about to get caught.</i>

30:46.424 --> 30:48.591
- So...what do you think?

30:48.693 --> 30:50.526
- I think you complain about
not being able to write,

30:50.595 --> 30:52.261
<i> but then you, you know,</i>
<i> drop everything</i>

30:52.363 --> 30:54.463
<i> for some medical emergency,</i>
<i> which, by the way,</i>

30:54.565 --> 30:56.031
<i> many believe to be</i>
<i> psychosomatic in origin.</i>

30:56.133 --> 30:58.834
- I meant about you...
coming over.

30:58.936 --> 31:00.903
- I wish I could.

31:00.972 --> 31:02.938
Ha. I wish I could, but I'm
just really busy right now,

31:03.007 --> 31:04.840
so...in fact, I should go.

31:04.942 --> 31:07.209
- Look, I know Peach
showing up was bad timing,

31:07.311 --> 31:09.378
but I wasn't exactly writing
when she showed up.

31:09.480 --> 31:12.248
- No, I know.
<i> Pro tip of the day:</i>

31:12.350 --> 31:14.750
<i> screen your calls when</i>
<i> you're trying to burn a body,</i>

31:14.852 --> 31:16.185
<i> because it turns out</i>
<i> things slip out</i>

31:16.287 --> 31:17.753
<i> that you didn't actually</i>
<i> wanna say.</i>

31:17.855 --> 31:19.488
I don't mean to be harsh,
but...you know

31:19.590 --> 31:20.856
you're sending
some mixed messages, right?

31:20.925 --> 31:22.191
- What is that
supposed to mean?

31:22.293 --> 31:24.260
- I'm--I'm trying
to do what you want,

31:24.362 --> 31:26.195
but I-I can't tell
what that is.

31:26.264 --> 31:27.930
<i> Like build you a bed,</i>
<i> be with you on the bed?</i>

31:28.032 --> 31:29.398
Drop you down the block
because your friend

31:29.500 --> 31:31.033
is asking, and not very
politely?

31:31.102 --> 31:32.935
<i> Seriously, Joe, shut up.</i>
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

31:33.037 --> 31:35.371
I have to go.

31:35.473 --> 31:37.072
- But--

31:37.808 --> 31:41.243
- Hey, how's it going?
- Good.

31:41.312 --> 31:43.212
That's one hell
of a bonfire.

31:44.815 --> 31:47.082
- Yeah, what can I say?
I went a little crazy.

31:47.184 --> 31:50.152
You know what, you're welcome
to join if you like.

31:50.254 --> 31:51.820
<i> Please say no.</i>
<i> Please say no.</i>

31:51.923 --> 31:54.456
- Oh, that would be great...

31:54.559 --> 31:57.092
but we need to get back
to the car

31:57.194 --> 31:58.694
before it gets any darker.

31:58.763 --> 32:00.429
Good luck.

32:00.531 --> 32:03.832
- Yeah, have a good one!
- You too.

32:03.901 --> 32:05.301
[low chatter]

32:05.403 --> 32:07.369
man: Did you remember
where you parked?

32:08.372 --> 32:11.040
<i> - I believe in love</i>
<i> at first sight.</i>

32:11.142 --> 32:12.908
<i> I had it with you, Beck.</i>

32:13.010 --> 32:16.378
<i> And maybe, just maybe,</i>
<i> I destroyed it</i>

32:16.447 --> 32:21.050
<i> just as fast, in the space</i>
<i> of a single phone call.</i>

32:21.152 --> 32:23.986
<i> Was all this for nothing?</i>

32:27.624 --> 32:29.324
[voice echoing]
"The king and queen,

32:29.393 --> 32:31.626
when they saw their
daughter..."

32:31.695 --> 32:34.930
<i> I've been calling Beck,</i>
<i> but...</i>

32:35.032 --> 32:36.598
<i> straight to voicemail.</i>

32:36.667 --> 32:38.633
<i> Worst three words</i>
<i> in the English language.</i>

32:38.735 --> 32:41.670
<i> I wonder what our kids</i>
<i> would have been like.</i>

32:41.738 --> 32:43.705
<i> They'd have grown up reading,</i>
<i> not glued to iPads,</i>

32:43.807 --> 32:45.140
<i> and we definitely</i>
<i> wouldn't have named them</i>

32:45.242 --> 32:46.641
<i> things like Gulliver</i>
<i> or Blaze</i>

32:46.710 --> 32:48.310
<i> or Misti with an "i."</i>

32:48.412 --> 32:51.613
<i> We would have crushed this.</i>
<i> Together.</i>

32:51.682 --> 32:54.850
<i> It wasn't supposed to</i>
<i> end like this.</i>

32:54.952 --> 32:57.385
<i> Call me back, Beck.</i>

32:57.488 --> 32:59.054
The end.

32:59.156 --> 33:01.957
<i> [somber music]</i>

33:02.025 --> 33:07.062
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:07.131 --> 33:09.631
<i> [trailing applause echoes]</i>

33:10.667 --> 33:13.535
- I don't mean this to blow
smoke up your ass or anything,

33:13.637 --> 33:15.937
but your writing
makes me think

33:16.039 --> 33:18.540
that Raymond Carver
has been reincarnated.

33:18.642 --> 33:21.042
- That is so kind of you
to say, Tomas.

33:21.145 --> 33:23.545
I was born in '88,
the year he died,

33:23.647 --> 33:25.247
so, weirdly enough,

33:25.315 --> 33:27.449
you're not the first
person to have said that!

33:27.518 --> 33:30.919
- Again, great work, Blythe.
Excited to see what's next.

33:31.021 --> 33:32.487
Beck, we weren't
expecting you.

33:32.556 --> 33:34.122
You didn't send along pages.

33:34.224 --> 33:36.057
- I know. I'm sorry.

33:36.160 --> 33:38.326
And I'm sorry I'm late.
It's just...

33:38.428 --> 33:41.296
I wrote them, but they
sounded super emo.

33:41.398 --> 33:42.797
So I wrote them up
and started over,

33:42.866 --> 33:44.799
and I lost track of time,
but, uh...

33:44.902 --> 33:47.469
this...feels like me

33:47.571 --> 33:50.305
and what I want to say.

33:51.742 --> 33:54.176
It's only one page, but--

33:54.278 --> 33:56.111
- That isn't really enough
for us to critique.

33:56.180 --> 33:59.381
- Are we supposed to
read it now...in front of you?

33:59.483 --> 34:01.183
[laughs] That's...
kind of awkward.

34:01.285 --> 34:03.084
- If that's the case,
I should warn you,

34:03.153 --> 34:04.553
I have this facial autism thing

34:04.655 --> 34:05.987
where I can't hide
what I'm thinking.

34:06.056 --> 34:08.256
[light laughter]
- Let's just reschedule

34:08.325 --> 34:11.026
your review
for another time.

34:14.298 --> 34:17.132
<i> [somber music]</i>

34:17.234 --> 34:23.905
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:33.984 --> 34:35.183
- Beck?

34:35.285 --> 34:37.786
- [inaudible]

34:37.888 --> 34:39.287
Hey.

34:40.857 --> 34:42.424
Uh...okay, so I hate
to admit it,

34:42.526 --> 34:43.792
but you were right.

34:43.860 --> 34:45.527
A little bit.

34:45.629 --> 34:47.696
I will do anything
for my friends,

34:47.798 --> 34:49.331
and do I hide behind them--
yeah.

34:49.399 --> 34:51.700
And do I use them as
an excuse not to write?

34:51.768 --> 34:54.069
Honestly, I'd use anything
as an excuse not to write,

34:54.137 --> 34:57.606
because...okay,
I'm afraid I might fail--

34:57.708 --> 34:59.541
one terrible page away

34:59.610 --> 35:01.910
from confirming I'm the worst
writer in history.

35:01.979 --> 35:05.480
All of that to say
if I'm sending mixed messages,

35:05.582 --> 35:09.217
it's because...
I don't know who I am.

35:09.286 --> 35:11.686
So how am I supposed to
know what I want?

35:11.755 --> 35:14.322
And I know--I know
I sound super gross,

35:14.391 --> 35:16.858
like so...
I don't know--millennial.

35:16.927 --> 35:19.194
Don't say anything.

35:19.263 --> 35:21.229
<i> - In this moment,</i>
<i> you are everything.</i>

35:21.331 --> 35:22.764
- Here's the thing.

35:22.866 --> 35:26.701
If you know who you are,
it's not like you share it.

35:26.803 --> 35:31.206
I mean, you're a Nice Guy with
the "You are remarkable" stuff

35:31.308 --> 35:33.842
and Feelings Guy with the
"Write what moves you."

35:33.944 --> 35:36.311
But then [lowers voice]
you try and go down on me

35:36.413 --> 35:37.679
in the middle
of a furniture store.

35:37.781 --> 35:39.080
If I didn't know better,

35:39.182 --> 35:41.049
I'd think you were hiding
something.

35:41.151 --> 35:43.785
For God's sakes, why are you
holding a Pendleton blanket?

35:46.623 --> 35:49.724
I've never even seen
your place.

35:49.793 --> 35:52.694
And you never talk about
any of your friends.

35:52.763 --> 35:54.729
I mean, who are you?

35:57.167 --> 36:00.302
Okay, that was too much.
Um...

36:00.370 --> 36:02.170
It sounded better
in my head.

36:02.272 --> 36:04.873
I wanna show you something.

36:04.975 --> 36:08.243
<i> [soft, sweeping music]</i>

36:08.345 --> 36:11.413
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:11.515 --> 36:13.982
You wanna know me, Beck?

36:16.053 --> 36:18.586
[hinges squeal]

36:18.689 --> 36:21.489
I'll show you
<i> exactly</i> who I am.

36:21.591 --> 36:24.626
<i> [dark music]</i>

36:24.728 --> 36:28.763
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:28.865 --> 36:31.266
<i> [ominous musical sting]</i>

36:31.368 --> 36:34.002
<i> [intense buildup]</i>

36:37.705 --> 36:40.906
- This is where we keep
the rarest books--

36:40.975 --> 36:43.509
the collectibles,
first editions.

36:43.611 --> 36:46.545
<i> [soft music]</i>

36:46.647 --> 36:49.548
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:49.650 --> 36:51.217
It's paper, cloth, leather,

36:51.319 --> 36:54.620
paste.
It's all vulnerable.

36:54.722 --> 36:56.689
All sensitive to light,

36:56.791 --> 36:58.524
humidity, temperature.

36:58.593 --> 37:02.361
<i> [soft music continues]</i>

37:02.463 --> 37:04.330
That's why...

37:04.432 --> 37:06.766
they need to be in here.

37:08.403 --> 37:10.035
[softly]
To protect them.

37:12.106 --> 37:13.672
I can take you
to my apartment.

37:13.775 --> 37:16.242
Anytime you want.

37:20.081 --> 37:22.148
I want you to meet
my friends, I do.

37:22.250 --> 37:25.484
But this...

37:25.586 --> 37:27.286
this right here

37:27.388 --> 37:31.257
is the most important
place in the world to me.

37:32.193 --> 37:35.694
As weird as it sounds...

37:35.797 --> 37:39.765
these books are more alive,

37:39.867 --> 37:43.135
more...worthy

37:43.237 --> 37:45.137
than most people I know.

37:47.408 --> 37:51.310
You wanna know who I am,
this is it.

37:51.379 --> 37:55.214
<i> [sweeping, emotional music]</i>

37:55.316 --> 38:02.555
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:12.600 --> 38:14.400
- There you are.

38:14.469 --> 38:18.103
- That's it. I am officially
out of the Tinder business.

38:18.206 --> 38:20.306
- [small laugh]
Bravo, honey.

38:20.408 --> 38:22.975
- I just--Oh, I feel like
this is a good step, you know?

38:23.077 --> 38:25.211
Like this is good for me.

38:25.313 --> 38:27.813
Joe is good for me.

38:27.915 --> 38:29.448
- Whatever you need,
Becks.

38:30.718 --> 38:34.186
No, I'm just saying--
and I mean this, honestly--

38:34.255 --> 38:36.956
maybe a simple life
isn't so bad.

38:37.024 --> 38:38.691
Maybe it's what you need.

38:38.793 --> 38:40.493
Maybe I should be
looking for that.

38:40.595 --> 38:42.795
- Joe isn't simple.
He's...he's different.

38:42.897 --> 38:45.331
Complicated.

38:45.433 --> 38:47.733
- That's funny...

38:47.835 --> 38:49.568
there's a book missing.

38:49.637 --> 38:52.571
- Really?
What book is that?

38:52.673 --> 38:54.173
- "Ozma of Oz."

38:54.275 --> 38:56.342
Huh. It was just here.

38:56.444 --> 38:58.944
Joe was looking at it
at my party.

38:59.046 --> 39:01.247
- I'm sure it'll turn up.

39:01.349 --> 39:03.849
<i> [edgy, anticipatory music]</i>

39:03.951 --> 39:09.788
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:11.959 --> 39:14.860
<i> - You've deleted Tinder,</i>
<i> and now you've called</i>

39:14.929 --> 39:17.129
<i> and asked me to come over.</i>

39:17.198 --> 39:23.002
<i> My faith in our epic love</i>
<i> story is officially restored.</i>

39:23.104 --> 39:24.670
- I'm sorry, Joe.
I'm so stupid.

39:24.739 --> 39:27.907
I left your list on my bed,
and Ron found it.

39:28.009 --> 39:30.009
I'm sorry.
- You're not stupid.

39:30.077 --> 39:33.178
It's not your fault.
- I tried to explain, but...

39:33.281 --> 39:36.148
- It's not your fault!

39:36.250 --> 39:37.550
[sighs]

39:37.618 --> 39:39.785
Guys like Ron are bullies.

39:39.854 --> 39:43.455
We just need to stay
one step ahead of them.

39:43.524 --> 39:46.458
Like the Musketeers--always
one step ahead of the Cardinal.

39:46.561 --> 39:47.860
Right?

39:47.962 --> 39:49.995
